title: [Whistler's Pass, Tunnel]
description: Pale moonlight filters in from a roughly oval opening in the tunnel wall.  Gusts of chill, mountain air and the fresh scent of forest growth enter through the tunnel opening, quickly dissipating in the stale air of the interior.  Over twelve feet in height, the opening appears large enough for use by even the largest of giantkin.
